README:

1.)  Copy all mailsync.* files to a location that can not be accessed remotely.
2.)  Install https://hg.nhg.name/unchroot/
3.)  Configure mailsync.conf.phs and make sure that all paths are accessible.
4.)  Configure mailsync.conf.example.phs and make sure that all paths are accessible.
5.)  mailsync.phs is called this way: sudo php mailsync.phs <user> <server>
5a.) mailsync.phs takes the configuration from mailsync.conf.<server>.phs
5b.) mailsync.phs copies the mail files via SFTP from /remote/path/<user> to /local/path/<user>
6.)  Configure CRON to call mailsync.phs regularly:
     */5 * * * * root php /path/to/mailsync.phs <user> <server> >/dev/null 2>&1
